340 g Pork Chops, boneless
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
1 unit(s) Carrot
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Mushrooms
1 unit(s) Lemon
1 unit(s) Green Onion
4 tbsp Teriyaki Sauce
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
11 g Asian Sesame Blend
1 tbsp Butter*
½ tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425°F. Wash and dry all produce.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, stir in rice, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, pat pork dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then pork. Pan-fry for 2-3 min per side, until golden.
Remove from heat, then sprinkle with half the Asian Sesame Blend all over.
Transfer pork to a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast in the top of the oven for 8-12 min, until cooked through.**
When done, rest pork, covered, for 5 min.
Carefully wipe the pan clean.

Peel, then halve carrot lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Quarter mushrooms.
Zest, then juice lemon.
Thinly slice green onion.
In a small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lemon juice, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lemon zest and 3 tbsp (6 tbsp) water.

Reheat the same pan (from step 2) over medium.
When hot, add half the sesame oil, then carrots and mushrooms. Cook for 2 min, stirring occasionally, until beginning to soften.
Add peppers. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp. Season with remaining Asian Sesame Blend, salt and pepper.

To the pan with veggies, add sauce (from step 3). Cook for 1-2 min, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.
Thinly slice pork and add to the pan with sauce and veggies, along with any pork resting juices. Stir to combine.

Fluff rice with a fork, then stir in half the green onions, remaining sesame oil and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter.
Divide rice between bowls. Top with saucy pork-veggie mixture.
Sprinkle remaining green onions over top.